| 11 | In distance vector routing the delay metric is | d. Queue Length |
| 12 | A well-defined groups that are numerically large in size but small compared to the network as a whole are used in | b. Multicast Routing |

---

## **Summary Table**

| Concept | Definition |
|--------|------------|
| Adaptive Algorithms | Change routing decisions dynamically based on network conditions. |
| Distance Vector Routing | Maintains and exchanges routing tables with neighbors. |
| Link State Routing | Builds a complete network map and computes shortest paths. |
| Hierarchical Routing | Uses intra and inter-domain routing to manage large networks efficiently. |
| Multicast Routing | Sends data to a specific group of receivers. |
| BGP | Enables inter-autonomous system communication. |
| Dijkstra’s Algorithm | Finds the shortest path in a network using a greedy approach. |

